The team here found a solution for this question using Eslint:
We added ESlint and some plugins as devDependencies and added this `"@typescript-eslint/consistent-type-imports": "error"` rule to the .eslintrc config file.

Now we've set up the IDE to fix on save with these VS Code settings:
```{
  "editor.codeActionsOnSave": {
    "source.organizeImports": "always",
    "source.fixAll.eslint": "always"
  }
}```
